Serves 4
There are 2 parts to this: meatballs, soup
/////
Meatballs:
  Mix the following in a bowl:
          500g chicken mince
          A bunch of tarragon, finely chopped (can add fresh dill, oregano, parsley too)
          1* egg yolk
          0.5* cup ricotta
          1.5* cup breadcrumbs
          Lemon zest
          Salt & pepper
  Line a tray with baking paper
  Roll the mince mix into little balls
  Fry the meatballs in batches so they brown all over
  Set aside (can also make ahead and keep in fridge until you need them)
/////
Soup:
  Using a pot with a lid
    Heat a little oil and add:
          1* chopped leek
          1* bulb of fennel
          10* cloves garlic
    Fry gently until softened
    Then add:
          2* chopped carrots
          About the same of diced celery
    Fry gently for a minute then add:
          2L chicken stock
    Bring to boil then simmer for about 5 minutes
    Add:
          1 cup orzo or a handfull of broken spaghetti
    Simmer until the pasta is al dente
/////
Bringing it together:
    Add the meatballs to the soup
    Add a squeeze of lemon juice
    Add some chopped herbs
    
